text:
45 tourists rescued from River Liffey cruise boat Original, timely global, travel, tourism, business news and research: 
Aug 16, 2015 eTN Exclusive: Unique and original, timely, global breaking news: 
DUBLIN, Ireland - Tourists on a River Liffey cruise boat this afternoon are getting a bit more action than they bargained for as they are currently being rescued by the fire brigade. 
It is understood the vessel lost power and struck a part of the bridge. 
The bridge has been closed off and Dublin Fire Bridgade swift water rescue crews from Tara Street and Phibsboro are in attendance.
